      "justification": "N5 is encrypted under the pre-shared symmetric key shk(A1,A2), known only to A1 and A2. The Dolev-Yao attacker cannot decrypt or derive the key from observed messages, as no key material or plaintexts are leaked. All protocol steps use the same key for encryption, but perfect encryption assumptions prevent any computational attacks. No protocol flaw allows the attacker to obtain N5.",
      "two_session_trace": "Session 1: A1 generates fresh N3, sends A1, {|N3|}shk(A1,A2) to A2. A2 receives, verifies, generates fresh N4, sends {|succ(N3),N4|}shk(A1,A2) to A1. A1 receives, sends {|succ(N4)|}shk(A1,A2) to A2. A2 receives, generates fresh N5, sends {|N5|}shk(A1,A2) to A1. A1 receives and terminates.\nSession 2: A1 generates fresh N3', sends A1, {|N3'|}shk(A1,A2) to A2. A2 receives, verifies, generates fresh N4', sends {|succ(N3'),N4'|}shk(A1,A2) to A1. A1 receives, sends {|succ(N4')|}shk(A1,A2) to A2. A2 receives, generates fresh N5', sends {|N5'|}shk(A1,A2) to A1. A1 receives and terminates."
    }
  ]
