  "analysis": [
    {
      "goal_id": 1,
      "goal": "a4 *->* A1: N7",
      "status": "no attack",
      "confidence": 93,
      "justification": "No attack is evident on the secure delivery of N7. N7 appears only in {|n11,N7|}K13, and the attacker cannot derive K13 because it is fresh from a3 and delivered only under protections based on K12 and shk(a3,a4), while K12 is itself protected by long-term shared keys. A1 also checks the fresh challenge N10 via {|N10|}K13, so replaying an old final message into another run does not satisfy the current run. Under Dolev-Yao assumptions, the attacker can relay messages but cannot forge or decrypt the required ciphertexts.",
      "two_session_trace": "Session 1: Honest run. A1 sends A1,a3,N5_1 to a2; a2 returns {|K12_1,A1,N8_1|}shk(a2,a3) and {|K12_1,N5_1,N8_1,a3|}shk(A1,a2). A1 forwards to a3 and receives from a3 {|K13_1,A1,N9_1|}shk(a3,a4),{|K13_1,N6_1,N9_1,a4|}K12_1. A1 sends a4 the ticket plus {|A1,N10_1|}K13_1, and a4 replies with {|N10_1|}K13_1,{|n11,N7_1|}K13_1. The attacker only relays and learns neither K13_1 nor N7_1.\nSession 2: Replay attempt. The attacker starts or observes a second run where A1 uses fresh values K12_2,K13_2,N10_2, then replays Session 1's final message {|N10_1|}K13_1,{|n11,N7_1|}K13_1 toward A1. A1 expects ciphertext under K13_2 containing N10_2, so the replay does not validate. Without K13_2, the attacker cannot forge a new valid final message or expose N7_2."
    }
  ]
}

